Package: PhIIdesign
Type: Package
Title: Sample Size Calculation for Phase II Designs
Version: 0.2.0
Maintainer: Koenraad D'Hollander <koenraad.dhollander@iddi.com>
Authors@R: c(
    person("Koenraad", "D'Hollander", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"), email = "koenraad.dhollander@iddi.com"), 
    person("IDDI Belgium", role = "cph"), 
    person("Elisabeth", "Coart", role = c("ctb", "cph")),
    person("Jan", "Wijffels", role = c("ctb", "cph")))
Description: Sample size calculations for designs of Phase II clinical trials. In particular techniques described in the following papers:
    'One-sample Multiple Testing Procedure for Phase II Clinical Trials' by Fleming (1982) <doi:10.2307/2530297>.
    'A Three-Outcome Design for Phase II Clinical Trials' by Sargent et al (2001) <doi:10.1016/s0197-2456(00)00115-x>.
    'Optimal Two-Stage Designs for Phase II Clinical Trials' by Simon et al (1989) <doi:10.1016/0197-2456(89)90015-9>.
    'Admissible Two-Stage Designs for Phase II Cancer Clinical Trials' by Jung et al (2004) <doi:10.1002/sim.1600>.
